item.title: [ENTESB-4099] A lot of warnings after installing RTGov in EAP log
item.description:
I can see a lot of warnings after installing RTGov into eap 6.4 with switchyard.

Firstly "using a private module which may be changed or removed in future versions without notice" and then a lot of "Only one Security Vault is supported. Change your configuration, please.". They are harmless, but if they can't be fixed somehow, it should be documented that they are just harmless warnings that do not affect the functionality.

item.summary: A lot of warnings after installing RTGov in EAP log

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Looks like the vault warning is a known issue: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1181457

The "Two vaults" error line is an EAP bug that is not fixed, so we'll have to live with it for the time being.
GSS has filed a note with docs to have something put in release notes, letting the user know a log filter is a good way to suppress the log lines.

https://issues.jboss.org/browse/FUSEDOC-979
Gary Brown Should this be marked as resolved now fix is in EAP?
Yes can be closed if fixed in EAP.
Verified with newer EAP and RTGov ER1

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
install eap 6.4, switchyard, integration pack, rtgov er3
start with standalone-full.xml
